headline: 'We were walking in blood': Iran's doctors recount crackdown on protesters
description: From crowded emergency rooms to apocalyptic scenes in Iranian cities, healthcare workers told Le Monde about the violence that descended on protesters calling for the end of the Iranian regime from January 8.

headline: Ukraine, Russia hold first direct talks on latest US peace plan
French PM survives two no-confidence votes over disputed budget
An era of distrust emerges between the US and its Western allies
description: Donald Trump's suggestion that the US could seize Greenland by force has exposed the strategic isolation his administration has chosen, in disregard for the country's commitments. Even though the Republican president abandoned the idea at Davos, the damage to US credibility is substantial.

headline: After Trump's retreat over Greenland, Europeans want to believe in their unity
description: Shaken by the unpredictability of the American president, the 27 member states declared at an extraordinary summit in Brussels on Thursday that they had learned lessons from the crisis, which saw them prepared to deploy the Anti-Coercion Instrument.

headline: Fewer French tourists are traveling to the US
description: Purchasing power, political climate: The number of French people traveling to the US dropped by 7% in 2025, though overall volumes remain high. For certain nationalities, there were even steeper declines: Germans dropped by 12%, and Canadians by 22%.

headline: 'The success of books by French politicians like Sarkozy and Bardella creates a dilemma for booksellers'
description: Books by right and far-right figures have been racking up extraordinary sales. Critics are divided over whether the current literary landscape reflects growing conservatism among French voters, observes Le Monde columnist Michel Guerrin.

description: Claude Le Roy, the former coach of Senegal, Cameroon, Ghana and Togo discusses the confusion that marred the Africa Cup of Nations final between Morocco and Senegal and the governance of world football.

headline: Is it ever a good idea to... wear aviator sunglasses (when you're Emmanuel Macron)?
description: In fashion, as in life, it is important to know the lines you should not cross. Or else, to do so deliberately.

headline: 'As it ceases to inspire, the US is losing part of itself'
description: Donald Trump's second term has turned the United States into a threat to which the rest of the world has no choice but to adapt. Yet, over the past eight decades, habits and practices have taken root that will be used to counter this new imperialism, writes Le Monde columnist Gilles Paris.
